I've never seen in any convention more harmony, such real fellowship and brotherly love. Another thing that I've done, I've met many new delegates of heaven, new brethren that I've had the privilege to shake hands with and talk to. It's an operation that could cut up some kind of a card up here or something, but it's like a plant. She'd have to sit there. I think she held that card for all the years now. And then it was brought here to me and showed me tonight. You know, I was saying, it's like bread upon the water, it returns to you when you try to do something for somebody else. Now, I have also had the privilege of meeting many of these fine ministers, And I certainly appreciate their fine fellowship and cooperation. Brother Carl announced me to be back next year, if the Lord is willing, and be here on earth. And I hope to meet every 1 of you here next year again. Each 1 bringing another delegate with me and with she. Now there is just 1 thing that I would like to say a little something about maybe for just a moment because Dr. Reed is to speak next and I've come all the way up here tonight, I've got 250 miles to make this trip to hear Dr. Reed. Just something happened a while ago that I would... But Dr. Reed, I drive a thousand miles to hear him. But something has... Since I've been here, I would drive a thousand miles just to hear what I heard a little while ago. Such a wonderful thing. Something that flesh and blood cannot reveal, it takes the Holy Spirit to do it. And to see someone who encouraged my life in such a way, And I certainly will be very grateful all the rest of my life. What I wanted to say was, if I ever have to have an operation, call on a medical doctor, you come to me, Dr. Reed, right away. I can trust a man to operate if I have to have 1, hands that lead to God. That would be the 1 I want working on me. So I trust I'll never have to have it. But if I do, I want a man like him to do the work, if he could be there. I had something that happened last night, or yesterday afternoon rather, that was really kind of strange to me. In that, every little thing has a meaning to me. But it was hard for me to believe that yesterday afternoon when I lost my tax up here. I tell you, I never once forgot in my life. Then my wife gave me a new Bible for Christmas. My old 1 was just born out. I've had it almost 20 years now. It was given to me by the Houston Gospel Tabernacle people many years ago when I started out on the campaigns. A man told me 1 time, it must be Brother Errol Cricket, beating up in New York, and I met a man, he said, say, what do you do with these business, man, being a preacher? I said, I'm a businessman. He said, what kind of business you're in? I said, assurance. Now he thought I said insurance. So I said assurance. He said, oh, what kind of assurance do you sell? I said, eternal life. I said, I don't want to sell it. I'm just a policy holder myself and I try to describe it to others. I remember a boy I went to school with 1 time and he was an insurance salesman. Now insurance is alright, But I don't have any, so he comes in my house and he said, Billy, I'd like to sell you some insurance that I know your brother, my brother sells for Metropolitan. He said, what's that I would, I'd like to sell you some insurance. I said, oh Wilbur, thank you. And you know, he may be your nicest brother. He writes articles in the Upper Room, this book, the Upper Room. So I said, I have assurance. He said, what? And my wife looked at me as if I was a hypocrite. She said, really? And I said, yes, I have assurance. He said, oh, I'm sorry, I heard you didn't have any insurance. And I said, no, I have assurance. And he caught me when I said that. He said, what did you say? I said, assurance. And he said, what do you mean? I said, blessed assurance. Jesus is mine. Oh what a foretaste of glory divine. I'm an heir of salvation, purchased of God, born of His Spirit, washed in his blood. He said, Billy, you know I appreciate that. That's a very good thing. But son, that will not put you out here in the graveyard. I said, but get me out. I'm not worried. I'm not bothered by getting in and getting out. So I think that's the way we deal with all this. I looked back and it wasn't there. I thought, well, I've got to misplace pages. Then my brother here, Brother Stanley, he came over, Bishop Stanley rather, And I don't know what the man meant. It was such a comfort hole. He walked up close to my side and said, hold steady, brother. God is maybe going to do something. And that just encouraged me to think. He had said, I wonder if he realized he prophesied. But talking to him a few moments ago, just before getting up here, I'm sure he did. So, I... Drawing in my message upon the birth pains and so forth, and my little rude way of doing it about the Lillie how it's born down and begotten and comes up and draws up the sun, the dew drop and so forth, and then the corruption of what it has to die out of, to be born out of, rather, to come out. And I was trying to make an illustration of the church. Just like the doctor here. If you went to treat a patient, we've got doctors today that says you can rub your foot on the back of the heel and heal a cancer on your face, you see. But a good doctor wouldn't listen to such a thing as that. He treats the patient according to the book that he's reading on medical research. And that's what I try to do to treat the patient. When I see the church sick, I don't want to try to tell them they need a new handshake or something like that in the organization. I have to treat it according to the book that I know to do. And so when I see the church look like breaking out with measles, I don't want to take the very prescription I think is right for the measles to get out of the church. When I see sin breaking out in it, it's the same way. I try to make a comparison with Esau and Jacob, and then bringing time down, and I won't go into that, but bringing it down to the last part, and my last scripture to use was comparing it, not unscripturally, but as Jesus said it would be, what the main doctor said the condition of the church should be in this last days, it would be a laodicea rich, blind, naked, poor church, and it would be compared with the days of Sodom. Now we know that's the truth. If you notice it historically, he brought in the days of Noah first, and then the days of Sodom. And that's just the way it's traveled, just the same way. History has many times, repeats itself. History has told us the promises of the Bible. For instance, like in Matthew 3 where it says, Out of Egypt I have called my son. Now if you run the reference on that, it was Jacob his son he called out of Egypt. That was his lesser son, but his great son Jesus was called out of Egypt too. So it had a compound answer. So Encina and I went along talking about that, And then I brought my thoughts of that and I walked off the platform and went out. My children were going home, wanted to stop out here somewhere to get a sandwich. And I went in and the wife said, Billy, I was so nervous, I didn't know what to do. So I gave you that Bible, I said, you never wrote it, and you never put it together, honey. She said, but this is the thing, I gave you a Bible that had a flaw in it. I said, well, maybe it wasn't. And so 1 of the children picked it up, and we peeled the pages, and oh, it looked all right. But right down at the bottom, it was 2 pages sticking together, see? And the 16th chapter was on this side, and then the continuation of the 16th chapter, come up on the other side, and the 17th started on the, see just perfectly exactly the same. Across, and that Indian paper, real thin, sticking together. And I was reading out the 17th chapter all the time, and then the 16th chapter. I thought, God, why did you do that? Why would there be such a thing now? That's me feeling in order to see what it was all about. Because I think nothing happens by chance. And I was thinking about the comfort of this brother here coming to tell me, hold steady. Him being a priest, hold steady. Maybe God is going to do something, or something in that manner. And I thought, how could that be? And then sitting there like a thunderbolt out of heaven, it came to me. This might not make sense to you, but it does to me. See, I remember in Luke, the fourth chapter, that Jesus entered the synagogue at Nazareth, where he was brought up at, as it's custom was to go into the church, the synagogue on the Sabbath. And what he did, we notice there, that the priest gave him the Bible, the scroll. Jesus, looking through the scroll, found a certain place, Isaiah 61, and he read the scripture. Then he handed the Bible back to the minister, and then as he turned to the audience, all eyes was upon him. And he said, this day, this scripture is fulfilled. And we know how peculiar that scripture reading was, because he just took a portion of the first and second verses of Isaiah 61, 1 and 2. But he read down this far, where the Spirit of the Lord is upon me, to bind up the brokenhearted and to heal the sick, and to open the blinded eyes, and to preach the acceptable dear of the Lord. And then he stopped. Or the next was to bring judgment. That would apply to his second coming, not his first coming. And he stopped, and turned around and said, This day, this scripture is fulfilled. How direct that was! And what a statement it was to the teachers and to the people that were present, that He could make this plain to the people, this day, this Scripture is fulfilled. For here He was, the Messiah, Yet they didn't believe it. Here he was, the anointed 1 for that hour. Every bit of his ministry from his birth up had proved to be what he was. And yet they could not believe it. What a statement! But he could say today, and if a person opened up their eyes, they could have known what day that they were living in, for that was his hour. For he was right there doing exactly what the scriptures, all the prophets had said had happened in that day. Here he was doing exactly what God had prophesied would happen. How did they miss seeing it? They should have known right quick, seeing what his ministry was, there's the Messiah. They would have known it because he said the scriptures fulfilled. I think of today, and notice what that was. As the priest gave the word over, The word was read and handed back to the priest. And the last quotation out of my text that I had in my scripture showdown was St. Luke 1730. Where Jesus referring back to this day that we're living in, rich Laodicea age, and yet rotten in politics, church politics, national politics, just as rotten as it could be. Every 1 of us knows it. He never said he was the son of God, he said he was the son of man. Now today he is the son of God, which he returned back and now he's in the form of the Holy Ghost, the unseen person, but yet God, the Son of God. In the Millennium, he sets upon his Father's throne, which he'll be Son of David. He revealed himself first as Son of Man, a prophet. Then they reached to the Church Age, Son of Man, or Son of God. And in the other age, son of David. 3 sons. But you notice here, he said, at the ending of the church age, it had gotten such a mess, until he would be revealed again as Son of Man. When the Son of Man is being revealed. How appropriate was that mix-up yesterday, and I hope you don't miss it. We have had the revelation of Son of God, but the last promise that Abraham had before the Son was made, or brought into existence, the 1 that He was promised before the promised Son showed up, God manifested Himself there at Sodom as a prophet, being a man in flesh. God, Elohim, as I heard someone speak a little while ago, which the Godhead bodily was in. He was the fullest, Elohim is the fullest of the Godhead bodily. So, notice what's taking place here. When he come up, how he made himself known. Could we not? Could I not say this if I'd just been on my toes? The brother prophesied when he said to me what he did. This day, this promise of this hour that we're now living in is fulfilled before our very eyes. He turned immediately to the congregation and 10 or 12, whatever people it was out there, unknowing, he did the very same thing he did at Solomon. This day has this scripture been made manifest before you. It's been made true before you. Then my brother and sister, delegates, ministers, whatever we are here, children of God, how close are we to His coming then? How close is the manifestation of the Scriptures like they did through Abraham bringing the Church up in type, which he was the promise to the Church. And now we find out Abraham's natural seed, how they failed, but the royal seed of Abraham, which is by faith in the promised Word, is now being manifested on the earth today. We are at the end time, my brothers and sisters. We are at the end. And we have not 1 other type. I have to type scriptures because I don't have an education enough to bring out words and things. I make a type, but if I see in the shadows, if I never had seen my hand and seen the shadow, I know I had 5 fingers. And that's why you have to watch the scripture types of the Old Testament. What does it do? It foreshadows this. And Jesus said that Sodom was the foreshadow of the end time now. And the very scriptures that was promised to Sodom, the very scriptures that were taken place to Sodom, that Jesus said would repeat itself again in this day, it's made known right before us today. God bless you. Don't miss it. And if I don't see you here next year, when you climb the golden stairs, I hope to meet you up there. God bless you. Father, we are, according to the Scriptures, we are seeing manifested before us the last sign in time. The words of Jesus Christ said this is so. Just as it was at Sodom. We see the world in its condition, we see the church in its condition, we see the elect being called out of every denomination. The life that's in those places moving out now to take the form of the seed. We pray, Heavenly Father, that we awaken it quickly. As a brother has just said now, he's seen before his face, and when he had his eyes closed, just masses going before him. Oh God, we feel that there's masses untouched yet. Help us, dear God. May we go from this condition with such a warning in our heart, knowing that this day the Scripture is fulfilled. In Jesus' name, Amen. Hallelujah. Our editor, Jerry, come up here. Let us agree together that God will heal this people that's sick. Dear Heavenly Father, we bring them into your presence by prayer. We know that 1 night there was an apostle that was shut off from all activities and he was in a jail and he was going to be beheaded the next day. Down at John Mark's house they had a prayer meeting and right in those inner cells there came that saint pillar of fire that followed the children of Israel, or the children of Israel followed it to the wilderness. Came right in because of that prayer meeting, and opened every door, and brought the apostle out on the street again, free to minister. We understand that these mis-ministered missionaries, people is bound in now, they're even in a coma. Lord, you are the same yesterday, today, and forever. Hear our prayer tonight, O God. You said when you pray, believe that you receive what you ask for, it shall be given. Lord, we believe. And pray that in Jesus' name that you'll heal them, Lord, for your glory. It's been said, been asked, now let it be done. Amen. Amen. God bless you. You believe that? Amen. Amen. You recognize that fellow? No, sir. A lot has changed since those days brother. He was a very handsome fellow. You're still handsome brother man. That's a nice picture. We had your aunt, Sister Ann, want me to go too. Maybe you'd like to say a word, Howard? In the name they left out, we all appreciate Brother Sha'Carrion normally every month. Receive what you ask for, it shall be given. Lord, we believe and pray that in Jesus' name that you'll heal them, Lord, for your glory. It's been said, it's been asked, now let it be done.
